propClasses: Override or extend the styles applied to the component.
propComponent:
The component used for the root node.
Either a string to use a HTML element or a component.
propFlexItem:
If `true`, a vertical divider will have the correct height when used in flex container.
(By default, a vertical divider will have a calculated height of `0px` if it is the child of a flex container.)
propLight: If `true`, the divider will have a lighter color.
stylesRoot: Styles applied to the root element.
stylesAbsolute: Styles applied to the root element if `absolute={true}`.
stylesInset: Styles applied to the root element if `variant="inset"`.
stylesFullWidth: Styles applied to the root element if `variant="fullWidth"`.
stylesLight: Styles applied to the root element if `light={true}`.
stylesMiddle: Styles applied to the root element if `variant="middle"`.
stylesVertical: Styles applied to the root element if `orientation="vertical"`.
stylesFlexItem: Styles applied to the root element if `flexItem={true}`.
stylesWithChildren: Styles applied to the root element if divider have text.
stylesWithChildrenVertical: Styles applied to the root element if divider have text and `orientation="vertical"`.
stylesTextAlignRight: Styles applied to the root element if `textAlign="right" orientation="horizontal"`.
stylesTextAlignLeft: Styles applied to the root element if `textAlign="left" orientation="horizontal"`.
stylesWrapper: Styles applied to the span children element if `orientation="horizontal"`.
stylesWrapperVertical: Styles applied to the span children element if `orientation="vertical"`.
